<subSubSection id="2CB49DD3D48A9AEB2B0114943EA8FFE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="206F22A54826E3555B47F2784D183660" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="D598426D78CBDE46E5AA00EB00994321" LSID="http://zoobank.org/B53F3D76-3549-4DD0-96BC-8BD848613381" authority="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari, 2022" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Balkanodesminus" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Balkanodesminus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Balkanodesminus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="EB39D3D1EE84A2EF90147582CB234D4B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="985C33D9D77234D81A73F57DF3D0A08B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type species">
<paragraph id="9924CF89710C4C3AAE19E9A5FBBFCF27" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7AF9C42C9E96BDD3393A8C3C41361B0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="8A4E450DDCB4F7B5A68FEA76CD2569B7" authorityName="Strasser" authorityYear="1962" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus bulgaricus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulgaricus">
<emphasis id="1CED6A94C9589B45B3EB62FE61F1A6A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Strasser, 1962, by present designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99032ED8A787DDF7D543050098ECC5D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CFEB83A8F8812A8466F4777A1116ACE4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00DA8CD7B30044811D8050899F856EEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differs from all European 
<taxonomicName id="D26F524C037E97531C04573A17AC035F" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1910" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trichopolydesmidae</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a characteristic acropodite of the gonopods divided into two parallel and mostly meso-laterally oriented branches, where solenomeral branch is transversely bipartite, consisting of slender solenomere and well-developed distal solenomeral process. The most similar genus is 
<taxonomicName id="C48A2B9233E171F4F2FFD9888634A079" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Rhodopodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhodopodesmus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2A56F6F73D239F8C02237F16FA45686D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rhodopodesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov., but it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="42B1501D24A5BB07ABE3BD61D29D9E6A" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Balkanodesminus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Balkanodesminus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E02780E31CF92533B3DC8E80293A22D6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Balkanodesminus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. and all other European 
<taxonomicName id="FFDEA58B60B74AA563ED16FE8F397A1C" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1910" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trichopolydesmidae</taxonomicName>
by the presence of trifid solenomeral branch (for more details see under 
<taxonomicName id="B2E07E1BFCA418EAE6DF459FF860AC19" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Rhodopodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhodopodesmus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6F8C9B0653DB7A66885756079CFE4E10" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rhodopodesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="568552AFD0C4D2A8AA6FCC76C345BCC9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">In addition, the diagnosis can be amended with the following combination of characters: small size (3.7-5.2 mm), 19 body rings (including telson), sensilla basiconica on antennomere 6 partially exposed outside the pit, hypoproct with more than two long distal setae, paraprocts with more than 2+2 long setae, metaterga with 4-8 irregular rows of trichoid setae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BF69505BAA6D4490A417D365DBE9C618" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="name">
<paragraph id="3A7B01EE0E510F98753E093B469C1555" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Name.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C00033930557A18CCB05ABA0DBFCEC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The new genus is named after the Balkan Mountains, its type locality, in combination with the suffix - 
<emphasis id="0B0BF836972407768843F0F394505A94" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">desminus</emphasis>
, as a diminutive of - 
<emphasis id="C83048701FE20324014F1690F527D01D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">desmus</emphasis>
, the common suffix in 
<taxonomicName id="55A1D84BF57401EA8E329D09FD0E5A42" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Rhodopodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="order">Polydesmida</taxonomicName>
, referring to the small size of its species, in contrast to confamiliar Dinaric 
<taxonomicName id="BBAC0F3AEDA604BC39D4B870B2753500" authorityName="Antic &amp; Reip" authorityYear="2014" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Balkanodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Balkanodesmus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="77743766F66EC141F71456469A10ED44" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Balkanodesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="E7B7CC7A128C999C6E22EDDC10B986D5" originalValue="Antić">Antic</normalizedToken>
&amp; Reip, in 
<bibRefCitation id="DB8701D7A4A5B16D05F0A661BB86F34F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3884.2.1" author="Antic, DZ" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="101 - 121" refId="B3" refString="Antic, DZ, Reip, HS, Drazina, T, Rađa, T, Makarov, SE, 2014. Three new monotypic genera of Trichopolydesmidae from Croatia, Balkan Peninsula (Diplopoda, Polydesmida). Zootaxa 3884 (2): 101 - 121, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3884.2.1" title="Three new monotypic genera of Trichopolydesmidae from Croatia, Balkan Peninsula (Diplopoda, Polydesmida)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3884.2.1" volume="3884" year="2014">
<normalizedToken id="8C8DB5C21498FFDFC7A6A377F2871CF6" originalValue="Antić">Antic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
, the largest Balkan trichopolydesmid. The name is a masculine noun.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
